                <strong>Step 2 :</strong> Evaluate community resources, protected areas, and divide community forests into management areas on a map(2017): <br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<i class="fa fa-arrow-right"></i>&nbsp;&nbsp; Achieve village map, current community forest map and future forest map, obtain data on trend analysis, calendar, season, match classification, species, diagram. <br>
                <strong>Step 3 :</strong> Survey of community forests in management areas (2017) : <br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<i class="fa fa-arrow-right"></i>&nbsp;&nbsp; Through the verification of the community forest management areas' boundaries with the participants, as well as the actual resource situation in each area, as well as the demarcation of the people's farmland on a scale map. <br>
            
                <strong>Step 4 :</strong> Demarcation of community forests as areas (2017) : <br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<i class="fa fa-arrow-right"></i>&nbsp;&nbsp; After disseminating forest resource assessment results Community demarcation of community forest management area. <br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<i class="fa fa-arrow-right"></i>&nbsp;&nbsp; The Aboun Leu community has defined five management areas: <br>
                1. Masot rice field covers an area of 1108 hectares, a type of rainforest, rich in wood species. <br>
                2. Andrach area: It covers an area of 406 hectares, which is a semi-dense forest and a small part of the rainforest forest, which is divided into sub-areas rich in species of klong chhlik, phchek rang, sralao, Sokrom. The first sub-region covers an area of 265 hectares, while the second sub-region covers an area of 141 hectares. <br>
                3. Anlong Chrouk Prey Souy area: 1399 hectares, a kind of klong chhlik, pheuk, pheuk, rang, sralao, Sokrom, especially bamboo. <br>
                4. Chong Kral area: 1038 hectares, rich in species of klong chhlik, pek phchek, rang sralao, Sokrom, especially odd bamboo.  <br>
                5. Sre Nai area: 577 hectares, a kind of klong chhlik tree, Phchek phchek, Reang Sokrom. <br>
                <strong>Step 5 :</strong> Community Forest Inventory(2017) :<br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<i class="fa fa-arrow-right"></i>&nbsp;&nbsp;Based on the results of the community forest inventory, the top five protected areas are as follows: <br>
                 1. Ochong Tral area, size 1038, has 388,212 seedlings, 20 to 29 cm in diameter, 40,3782 trees, 30 cm in diameter, up to 38,406 trees. <br>
                 2. Land size: 406, there are 643916 seedlings, 10 to 29 trees, 198940 trees, 30 cm trees, up to 23954 trees.<br>
                 3. Sre Masot, size 1108, has 245976 seedlings, 10 to 29 trees, 69804 trees. Ore Sre Nay, size 577, has 246956 seedlings, 10 to 29 trees, 132710 trees, 30 cm trees, up to 28273 trees. 5. Anlong Chrouk Prey Suy has a land size of 1399 hectares, has 941527 seedlings, 10 to 29 trees, 48,4054 trees, 30 trees up to 88,137 trees. <br>

